Kelvin Ekerete The management, players, and staff of Nigeria Professional Football League side, Plateau United, are in mourning after the death of the teamâ€™s assistant coach, Audu Pele, on Wednesday. Pele, who died Wednesday afternoon at his residence, has been laid to rest according to Islamic rights. The deceased, who is survived by a wife and five children, joined Plateau United as a coach of the feeder team in 2014 and gradually moved up the ranks to become first-team coach and was in an acting capacity when head coach, Abdu Maikaba, was away on national duty with the Flying Eagles. Meanwhile, the management has declared Thursday (today) as a training-free day as a mark of respect for their departed official. Copyright PUNCH.
